<br>
I kept saying l, r and the japanese ro sound... and I figured out what the differences between the three are...<br>
<br>
l sound -&gt; is made by vibrating the vocal chords and then having the tounge tip at the front part of the roof of the mouth... and then pulling the tounge away. of course it happens so fast... that its 'l' as we normally know it. The tounge tip touches the teeth front as well.<br>
<br>
the japanese sound -&gt; half way between l and r.. its a sound made like the l.. except the tounge kinda vibrates and the teeth are not touched with the tip of the tounge.<br>
<br>
the r sound -&gt; doesn't touch the roof of the mouth at all.. and it starts the furthest back... but in a position otherwise similar to l and ro.<br>
<br>
the differences occur in the first 5 ms or so of the sound...<br>
<br>
alot like D and B.... very clearly distinct letters... but most of the sound is 'E'<br>
<br>
right :) just thought I'd write all this... coz I'm... ... strange ;)<br>
